summaries.short: When a major client stops trading with Pierpoint, the recent graduates are presented with a new opportunity to recover lost business.
summaries.full: When Pierpoint loses a major client, the grads face their most challenging--and potentially rewarding--test to date: devising pitches to drive new business. A creative Gus partners with Robert to catch Clement's attention. Meanwhile, as she navigates a complicated living situation with Yasmin, Harper attempts to juggle conflicting requests from Eric and Daria.

summaries.short: After her birthday celebration gets out of hand, Harper learns that a discrepancy in her work stands to cost her team a fortune.
summaries.full: After a wild birthday celebration with Robert, Yasmin, and Greg, Harper's workday spirals out of control. As a discrepancy in one of her trades puts her team at risk for major losses, Harper seeks support from a surprising source, while unexpected trouble at a networking event brings Yasmin and Robert closer, and Gus further alienates his coworkers.

summaries.short: A disastrous combination of drugs, alcohol, and inappropriate confrontations derails Pierpoint's appreciation dinner for its new graduates.
summaries.full: With Harper struggling to find her feet in a new city, Pierpoint throws a morale-boosting appreciation dinner which sees her challenging a drunken, irate Kenny while Gus alienates senior management by discussing his team's future. Meanwhile, Yasmin comes face to face with the culture of her new team and takes her flirtation with Robert to risky new heights.

summaries.short: When Pierpoint is rocked by a former employee's scathing expose, the grads use it as an opportunity.
summaries.full: As Pierpoint is shaken by a former employee's scathing expose, Eric goes offsite for the day, prompting an unauthorized Gus to cover trades from his desk, while Harper maneuvers her way into a meeting with one of Eric's coveted, disgruntled ex-clients. But when Gus and Harper both cross the line, they risk compromising their futures at the bank.

summaries.short: Series premiere. Ambitious young grads angle for permanent positions at the preeminent London investment bank Pierpoint & Co.
summaries.full: Series premiere. Five young graduates do whatever it takes to make themselves indispensable at preeminent London investment bank Pierpoint & Co. As hungry outsider Harper grapples with a decision that will gravely affect her future at the bank, she and party-boy Robert take very different approaches to their first few weeks in the bank.

summaries.short: Sex, drugs, and secrets light up Pierpoint's annual holiday party. Later, Harper is pulled into a meeting with the company's president.
summaries.full: Sex, drugs, and secrets light up Pierpoint's annual holiday party, where Maxim's unexpected arrival aggravates tensions between Yasmin and Kenny, and Greg finds himself in a painful predicament after partying a little too hard with Robert and Usman. After confiding in Daria, Harper is blindsided by a meeting with Sara, the president of the London office.
